title: How to Dual Boot Linux Mint and Windows 10 [2019] Easily
description:
Dual boot means you can have more than one operating system in one system and you can choose which OS you want to use at the boot time.

In this tutorial, I am going to show you how you can install Popular Linux Distribution Mint alongside Windows 10 in dual boot. So that you will be able to use both Linux Mint and Windows on the same system.
 
I Feel that dual booting Linux mint with Windows is the best way to enjoy both the operating systems.

Newer Desktops, Computers and Laptops support secure UEFI boot so you don't have to disable fast boot or secure boot anymore. Installing Linux mint and Windows in the same system has become a lot easier and hassle free.

Still it is recommended to making a backup of your data on an external hard disk, keep a Windows 10 bootable USB or a Grub repair disk with you to avoid any unfortunate events.

Zorin OS is designed to be easy, so you won't need to learn anything to get started. The Zorin Appearance app lets you change the desktop to resemble the environment you're familiar with, whether it's Windows, macOS or Linux.

Thanks to Linux's advanced security features, Zorin OS is resistant to viruses. Security patches and software updates are available for years to come.

Built on an Ubuntu Linux foundation, Zorin OS runs on the same Open Source software that powers the U.S. Department of Defense, NASA, and more.

description:
WHAT AN ACTUAL LUXURY! ü•∫ my UK family came to visit my US University in San Francisco!! I don't know if anyone else feels like this, but I think one of the worst things about being an older sibling away is feeling like you're missing out on your younger sibling growing up. Today's episode also has a spin on homesickness (08:12 to chat about it + advice).

I go to Minerva University in San Francisco! It's a super new, international programme and I bloody love it :)

Where to go in San Francisco:
- The Mission District (try a taco/burrito place, go to Mission Dolores Park, Clarion Alley, Balmy Alley, get boba from Boba Guys)
- Embarcadero (enjoy the views from the pier of the bay, go to Pier 39 for sea lions and views of Alacatraz). Walk all the way down Market Street to get here for a good view of the financial district!
- Twin Peaks (the incredible viewpoint we went to!)
- Corona Heights is also an AMAZING viewpoint in the centre of the city; best at night
- Haight-Ashbury: go to the shop Love on Haight for hippie glitter. Go thrifting! Chill in Buena Vista Park or walk through the Panhandle to Golden Gate Park/
- Golden Gate Park! Climb Strawberry Hill, go to the lake, Academy of Sciences + Japanese Tea Garden + De Young Museum are more tourist attractions available there!
- Civic centre for the SF Symphony or SF Ballet! if you're a student, sign up to SF Art and Film for free tickets üëè
- Land's End and Sutro Baths!
- China Beach
- Golden Gate Bridge (sunrise is a MUST. don't be alarmed by the fog!)
- Chinatown! Try some dumplings, enjoy the views and the culture of the oldest Chinatown in the world.
- The Castro! Great nightlife, LGBTQ+ district of SF, expect naked men walking dogs. You've been warned ü§∑‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è

title: what i'm doing in uganda!! last minute pack with me :)
description:
For 3 months, I headed on the programme ICS to work with the charity Restless Development in Uganda!! In this very quick video (where I pack for Uganda literally at the LAST minute because I suck at being organised...!!), I discuss some of the issues around volontourism, international development and white saviourism - I also really encourage you to do your own research! Especially if you're interested in volunteering abroad, it's so important to be well-informed on where your money's going and how a charity operates, as well as social issues if entering black spaces as a white person!! I love the IG page @nowhitesaviors.

I'm now officially back from Uganda (ayyyy) and will be posting the vlogs v v soon!

ICS (international citizen service!) is a UK-government funded programme. You have to successfully get through the interviews before fundraising ¬£800, attending a 4-day training camp and then doing in-country training too! I love it because community leaders in rural Uganda guide the nature of the work and request the charity be there in their village!! Restless also train the same number of Ugandan volunteers, who join up with us to form one big team; it's a cross-cultural working relationship!  A pet, or companion animal, is an animal kept primarily for a person's company or entertainment rather than as a working animal, livestock or a laboratory animal. Popular pets are often considered to have attractive appearances, intelligence and relatable personalities, but some pets may be taken in on an altruistic basis (such as a stray animal) and accepted by the owner regardless of these characteristics.

Two of the most popular pets are dogs and cats; the technical term for a cat lover is an ailurophile and a dog lover a cynophile. Other animals commonly kept include: rabbits; ferrets; pigs; rodents, such as gerbils, hamsters, chinchillas, rats, mice, and guinea pigs; avian pets, such as parrots, passerines and fowls; reptile pets, such as turtles, alligators, crocodiles, lizards, and snakes; aquatic pets, such as fish, freshwater and saltwater snails, amphibians like frogs and salamanders; and arthropod pets, such as tarantulas and hermit crabs. Small pets may be grouped together as pocket pets, while the equine and bovine group include the largest companion animals.

Pets provide their owners (or "guardians")[1] both physical and emotional benefits. Walking a dog can provide both the human and the dog with exercise, fresh air and social interaction. Pets can give companionship to people who are living alone or elderly adults who do not have adequate social interaction with other people. There is a medically approved class of therapy animals, mostly dogs or cats, that are brought to visit confined humans, such as children in hospitals or elders in nursing homes. Pet therapy utilizes trained animals and handlers to achieve specific physical, social, cognitive or emotional goals with patients.

A Netherland Dwarf rabbit on swing
People most commonly get pets for companionship, to protect a home or property or because of the perceived beauty or attractiveness of the animals.[2] A 1994 Canadian study found that the most common reasons for not owning a pet were lack of ability to care for the pet when traveling (34.6%), lack of time (28.6%) and lack of suitable housing (28.3%), with dislike of pets being less common (19.6%).[2] Some scholars, ethicists and animal rights organizations have raised concerns over keeping pets because of the lack of autonomy and the objectification of non-human animals.[3]

description: I had to do a video, the boxes were starting to pile up!!!!! Plus I got a new table to record unboxing and reviews with!!!!!!

description: Yeah I'm not dead!!!! I finally decided to unbox in front of my camera, nothing major just some pops. Also my cats are curious so you'll see them running around in the background

description: hi there I got some mystery mini from the recent Hot Topic Hot Cash event and so I wanted to do a video about unboxing some cute vynl figures :3

description: Yup yup it's another unboxing from a recent Hot Topic order. It came in today and i was like why not!!!

description: I forgot to upload this, it's max and the Doods opening Christmas gifts and gifts from the PO Box. MAAAAAAALLLLLLLLLEEEE TTTTIIIIIIIMMMMMEEEE Christmas edition!!! I also sent max and them gifts, their reactions made me smile so much :)

title: Black Friday Unboxing
description: Sorry about the odd noises my head is spinning from wrapping up gifts and dealing with petty family problems. My god my hands look puffy I feel bad.....

title: Random Unboxing
description: Decided to do a random unboxing of some convention stuff I picked up with some good coupons. Winter is Coming!!!!

description: So I am trying out Sony Vegas for video editing and I would like some feedback on it, first time using it!!!!

title: Draco Plays Halo 3 Halo The Master Chief Collection Gets a Par Time For The First Time!
description: That's right more Halo 3 goodness, managed to record two missions with my friend and for the first time got a par time on a mission :3

title: Target Unboxing
description: Well I decided to show off my recent pop hunt from Target with this unboxing, I hope you all have a good Friday the 13th!!!!!

title: Late Night Unboxing
description: Just a random unboxing video before the weekend, it's been really hot lately, but I am still here!!!!!

title: Draco Plays Halo The Master Chief Collection Halo 3 Tsavo Freeway Mission
Draco Plays Halo The Master Chief Collection Halo 3
description: So now we are playing Halo 3, I am really impressed with how they made everything in HD, now if they could update the game...

title: Draco Plays Halo The Master Chief Collection Halo 2 Finale
description: Here we are me and my friend finally finish Halo 2 after a huge delay. I know I know there's no commentary, but the thing we dont tlak much during the game and I don't want people being like why dont you talk more? Because when I game I focus on playing and I dont feel the need to talk.  Also started playing Halo 3, more videos incoming!

title: Carherine   Draco Plays Catherine Part 01 Enter The Stray Sheep
description: So yeah my cables finally came in and now I don't need Audacity to do my commentary anymore!!! I got a headset that works well with the elgato and man it sounds alot better!!! More Videos Incoming!!!! Let e know what you think of the audio!!!

title: My Pop In A Box Unboxing
description: My Pop In A Box order came today!!! First time ordering from this site and I have to say that it was worth the price only 30 bucks!! Hopefully most of you got this in time or were able to afford it!!!

title: Cinco De Mayo Funko Pop Boxing
description: Happy Cinco De mayo Doods!! Finally did an unboxing video as Cinco De Mayo is on. Really happy with these recent purchases that were made last month and they arrived this month :)

title: My Latest Funko Pop Haul and Camera Update 2
description: So yeah even though I recorded this on Thursday I couldn't upload it until today since I needed to get a new usb cable for the camera and it worked!! i can transfer the videos and pictures from the camera with ease. I can't wait to do more,i can make better quality customization videos now!! Let me know how the quality is :)

title: My Funko Pop Haul and Unboxing From My Vacation
description: So I finally got to unboxing this huge box of pops I got from my vacation with Koari. I swear I should have recorded his reaction to how many I got, it was priceless. I managed to have enough energy to film and edit this video, i edited most of my breathing since i didn't want you guys to hear me huffing and puffing like a windbag. Anyway i hope this turns out good :)
